  "title": "1. Variables & Data Types",
  "sections": [

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "1. Definition"
    },
    {
      "type": "definition",
      "text": "Variables in Python are used to store data values. Python is dynamically typed, meaning you don’t need to declare the type explicitly."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "👉 Type is decided at runtime\n👉 Variables are created on assignment\n👉 No need to declare data type"
