{
  "title": "2. Decorators & Generators",
  "sections": [

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "1. Decorators"
    },
    {
      "type": "definition",
      "text": "A decorator is a function that modifies the behavior of another function without changing its original code."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "👉 Used for logging, authentication\n👉 Helps avoid code repetition\n👉 Uses @ syntax"
    },

    {
      "type": "image",
      "heading": "Decorator Working Diagram",
      "url": "https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-4/y8JViimh896IMqmSlZalSLQIgz2gGEu9_lEE8fE-xttz5bMpfr7QEJbjhjR3JtdyeyaBhquJJ9lzG7AXWogFoc_kU-_L8e7ulRN6PKlWfzwA1um9OygDSF0wsxEMNEJpiXrKx4lKYw9hPp1lxpMvFdBF8wY8SrmGwHyvxPBe62Q?purpose=inline"
    },

    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "A decorator takes a function, wraps it, and returns a new function with added behavior. It does not modify the original function directly. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}"
    },

    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "def my_decorator(func):\n    def wrapper():\n        print(\"Before\")\n        func()\n        print(\"After\")\n    return wrapper\n\n@my_decorator\ndef hello():\n    print(\"Hello\")\n\nhello()"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "2. Advantages of Decorators"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Code reusability",
        "Clean and readable code",
        "Avoid duplication",
        "Easy to extend functionality"
      ]
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "3. Generators"
    },
    {
      "type": "definition",
      "text": "A generator is a function that returns values one by one using yield instead of returning all values at once."
    },

    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "👉 Uses yield keyword\n👉 Memory efficient\n👉 Generates values lazily"
    },

    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Generator functions pause execution at each yield and resume later, maintaining their state. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}"
    },

    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "def count(n):\n    for i in range(n):\n        yield i\n\nfor num in count(3):\n    print(num)"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "4. Generator Working"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "👉 Execution pauses at yield\n👉 Continues from same point on next call\n👉 Works like iterator"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "5. Generator vs Function"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Function → return",
        "Generator → yield",
        "Function → returns all at once",
        "Generator → returns one by one",
        "Generator is memory efficient"
      ]
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "6. Key Points"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Decorator modifies function behavior",
        "Generator produces values lazily",
        "Both are advanced Python concepts",
        "Important for interviews"
      ]
    }

  ]
},

{
  "title": "3. Error Handling",
  "sections": [

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "1. Definition"
    },
    {
      "type": "definition",
      "text": "Error handling in Python is used to manage runtime errors (exceptions) so that the program does not crash and continues execution smoothly."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "👉 Exceptions are runtime errors that interrupt normal program flow\n👉 Python provides try, except, else, finally to handle them\n👉 Helps in building robust and fault-tolerant applications"
    },

    {
      "type": "image",
      "heading": "Exception Handling Flow",
      "url": "file_000000003d3c7206ad137f586255f59b"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "2. How Exception Handling Works"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "When an error occurs inside try block, Python searches for a matching except block. If found, it executes that block; otherwise, the program stops. finally block always executes. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "3. Types of Errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Syntax Error → occurs before execution",
        "Runtime Error (Exception) → occurs during execution",
        "Logical Error → incorrect output without error"
      ]
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "4. try-except Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "try:\n    x = int(input())\nexcept ValueError:\n    print(\"Invalid input\")"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "5. Multiple Exception Handling"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "try:\n    x = int(\"abc\")\nexcept ValueError:\n    print(\"Value Error\")\nexcept TypeError:\n    print(\"Type Error\")"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "6. else and finally"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "try:\n    x = 10 / 2\nexcept:\n    print(\"Error\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Success\")\nfinally:\n    print(\"Always executes\")"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "7. Raise Exception"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "if age < 0:\n    raise ValueError(\"Invalid age\")"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "8. Custom Exception"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "python",
      "code": "class MyError(Exception):\n    pass"
    },

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "9. Key Points"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "try block → risky code",
        "except → handles error",
        "else → runs if no error",
        "finally → always executes",
        "raise → create exception"
      ]
    }

  ]
},
