{
  "title": "6. NumPy Basics",
  "sections": [

    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "1. Definition"
    },
    {
      "type": "definition",
      "text": "NumPy (Numerical Python) is a powerful Python library used for numerical computations. It provides support for large multi-dimensional arrays and matrices along with mathematical functions to operate on them."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "👉 Used in Data Science, Machine Learning, AI\n👉 Faster than Python lists\n👉 Supports high-performance operations"
